      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:5:160",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/2/103",
      "text": [
        " «يَحُجُّ بِهَا بَعْضُهُمْ وَ كُلُّهُمْ شُرَكَاءُ فِي اَلْأَجْرِ » فَقَالَ لَهُ لِمَنِ اَلْحَجُّ، فَقَالَ «لِمَنْ صَلِيَ فِي اَلْحَرِّ وَ اَلْبَرْدِ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2241 - Ali ibn Yaqtin asked Imam Abu Al-Hasan (as) about a man who entrusted the cost of one Hajj to five people.\nImam (as) replied: \"One of them performs the Hajj, and all of them share in the reward.\"\nAli ibn Yaqtin then asked: \"Who is the Hajj attributed to?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"It is for the one who prayed in both the heat and the cold.\""
        ]
      }
    },
